    {
      "id": "23fc484c0bee8f51124117403abb2f44335a6498",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2014-06-27 07:12:52.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\n(3 comments)\n\nI don't mind many of the fixes here, but I think there is a more serious problem with why the client doesn't disable ACL support when the MDT does not return OBD_CONNECT_ACL?  \n\nAccording to mdt_init0() the MDT should only set mo_acl = 1 if MNTOPT_ACL is returned from the OSD.  In osd-ldiskfs::osd_conf_get() it returns MNTOPT_ACL only if the filesystem was mounted with \"-o acl\" (the default), but it seems that osd-zfs::osd_conf_get() it always returns MNTOPT_ACL.\n\nIt would be better to not return MNTOPT_ACL if ZFS is mounted with \"-o noacl\" so that the clients don't send ACL requests to the MDS at all.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
